description:
In this episode, we explore the legacy of John Wycliffe - someone who has often been referred to as the Morning Star of the Reformation. We travel to Lutterworth, which was John's workplace, and where he completed his most significant work - uncovering the great impact that he had on the Reformation. Educated at Oxford University, Wyliffe was a scholar, and an unrivalled debater. It was whilst he was a student that he first incurred the displeasure of Rome. He went on to take the reference 'Morning Star', which suggested that he was a reformer before the term became popular. He stood alone as a voice of change, and called people back to the Bible. 

To find out more information about John Wycliffe visit our in depth article.
